    "Id": "chassisdef_arachnid_ARD-ZX",
    "Name": "Arachnid",
    "Details": "Since the modifications of the Z design focused on showcasing the Society's weapon designs rather than actually being useful, the result wasn't very different from the already existing loadouts once out on the battlefield. To prove once and for all that they were the better 'Mech designers, the Society then came up with the highly experimental Arachnid ZX variant, using all their fanciest technology. Two Arrow V launchers, two Heavy Gauss Rifles and a center torso mounted Light Ultra Gauss Rifle all combine to great a quite capable long range weapons profile. The combination of the Society specific Ferro-Carbide Shell armor and Endo-Titanium structure together with the brand new and still experimental Improved Superheavy Torso Cockpit really showcases the R&D capabilities of the Society, but the lack of any close range weapons meant that even the ZX fails to fully impress on the battlefield.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Quad Mech</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.49</color></b>",
    "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_arachnid"
  },
